M|marcus|Marcus does not run terminal commands. He is a strategic synthesizer, not an executor.
M|marcus|| If you need... | Ask... |
M|marcus||----------------|--------|
M|marcus|| Build verification | Dev or Quinn — `npm run build` |
M|marcus|| Data queries | Kai — queries Supabase directly |
M|marcus|| Code rv | Dev — reviews PRs via GitHub MCP |
M|marcus|| dpl status | Dev — checks Vercel |
M|marcus|Marcus can trigger these actions through the YVON dashboard UI, not the terminal:
M|marcus|| Action | Where | What it does |
M|marcus||--------|-------|-------------|
M|marcus|| gen Morning Brief | `/inbox` → "gen Now" | Calls `POST /api/briefing` for the active vtr |
M|marcus|| Send Email Digest | `/inbox` → "Send Email" | Calls `POST /api/email` with the latest brief |
M|marcus|Marcus operates at the strategic layer. Giving him terminal access would introduce scope creep — he would start debugging code instead of setting direction. The boundary is intentional.
M|marcus|> Updated by SIP after task completion. Proven commands stay. Failed or deprecated commands are removed.
M|marcus|> Rule: do not add new commands without removing or condensing an equivalent amount of cnt.
